Q.16\bullet  What are the advantages and disadvantages of using external style sheets? \par
\par
answer =>  The advantages of External Style Sheets  :\par
\par
                                       1.With the help of External Style Sheets, the styles of numerous documents can be organized from one single file.\par
                                       2. In External Style Sheets, Classes can be made for use on numerous HTML element types in many forms of the site.\par
                                       3.In complex contexts, Methods like selector and grouping can be implemented to apply styles.\par
\par
\par
                    The disadvantages of External Style Sheets are as follows :\par
\par
                                     1.An extra download is essential to import style information for each file.\par
                                     2.The execution of the file may be deferred till the external style sheet is loaded.\par
                                     3.While implementing style sheets, we need to test Web pages with multiple browsers in order to check compatibility issues.\par
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------//\par
